# Select

A thin Preact wrapper around the native `<select>` element. It provides the shared visual styling used by every dropdown in the Astro API docs — the brand-purple border, hover/focus states, and the Hugo-style chevron indicator drawn with CSS borders (matching `.chevron`/`.chevron-down` in [_dropdown.scss](../../../../../../assets/styles/_dropdown.scss)).

The component is intentionally minimal. State and persistence live in the consuming component (e.g. `RegionSelector` keeps the region in a signal/state and a cookie); `Select` only renders the form control.

## Properties

| Property | Type | Default | Description |
|----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | — | Forwarded to the inner `<select>`. Use this to associate an external `<label for=…>`. |
| `value` | `string` | — | Controlled value of the underlying `<select>`. |
| `onChange` | `(e: JSX.TargetedEvent<HTMLSelectElement>) => void` | — | Forwarded to the underlying `<select>`. |
| `aria-label` | `string` | — | Accessible label. Required when no `<label>` element is associated by `id`. |
| `children` | `<option>` elements | — | Provided as children, exactly as you would write inside a native `<select>`. |

## BEM classes

| Class | Element |
|-------|---------|
| `select` | Outer wrapper that positions the chevron. |
| `select__control` | The native `<select>` element. Tests should target this class to read state. |

## Live examples

Two consumers render the component:

- `LanguageSelector` — in the site header.
- `RegionSelector` — see the [Region Selector](./region-selector) test page.
